article.headline: Stetson 73, Lipscomb 71
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon scored 19 points and hit two free throws with 4 seconds left as Stetson overcame a 15-point second half deficit to beat Lipscomb 73-71 on Saturday. Lipscomb (11-10, 6-8 Atlantic Sun Conference) held a 38-36 halftime lead and stretched it 57-42 with 14:14 left on a jumper by Brian Fisk, who finished with 19 points. But Stetson (10-12, 8-7) used a 7-0 run to tie the game at 66 with 5:55 left. The Bisons thought they would have the final shot after Anthony Register, who finished with 21 points, missed a layup for the Hatters with under a minute to play. But Gordon, who also had 10 rebounds and three steals, stripped Fisk with 4 seconds left and was fouled immediately. After he hit both free throws, Fisk had a chance to win the game for Lipscomb on a 30-foot shot in the final second, but the ball never touched the rim. Will Holloman scored 14 points and Karl Hollingsworth added 13 for Stetson. Lipscomb's Jason Guyette had 12 points.
